<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860d.01/8: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Commission to
                                        Negotiate Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-19T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            19, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>792. Is Department correct in assuming that you will answer direct
                                Stockholm Legation’s telegram No. 100, February 15 to you regarding
                                recognition of Finland?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>